=== Subsidiary Shrines ===
;Sessha Muraya Shrine (むらやじんじゃ)
: A Shikinaisha. Enshrined deities: {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|Q2564508|qid=Q2564508|lt=Ame-no-Koyane no Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane}}, {{ill|qid=Q1107286|lt=Futsunushi|Q1107286|qid=Q1107286|qid=Q1107286|lt=Futsunushi no Kami|1=Futsunushi}}, {{ill|lt=Himegami|Q22070227|qid=Q22070227|lt=Hime no Ōkami|1=Himegami}}, {{ill|qid=Q1502690|lt=Takemikazuchi|Q1502690|qid=Q1502690|qid=Q1502690|lt=Takemikazuchi no Kami|1=Takemikazuchi}}, as well as Ōtomo no Takemochi no Muraji and Muroya no Muraji.
: Formerly located on the riverside east of the current site at the place name Miyanoyama, but it was destroyed by warfare in {{ill|lt=Tenshō|Q1145058|qid=Q1145058|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 12 and subsequently relocated to the present shrine grounds.
;Massha Hattori Shrine (はっとりじんじゃ)
: A Shikinaisha. Enshrined deities: {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Minakanushi|Q2842779|qid=Q2842779|lt=Ame-no-Minakanushi no Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Minakanushi}}, {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Mihoko|Q119380365|qid=Q119380365|lt=Ame-no-Mihoko no Mikoto|1=amenomihokonomikoto}}.
: Formerly located at Kakimori in Ōaza Daianji, it was destroyed by warfare during the Nanboku-chō period and relocated to the present shrine grounds in Tenshō 1 ({{ill|lt=1573|Q6678|qid=Q6678|1=1573}}).
;Sessha Kusumi Shrine (Wakamiya Ebisu Shrine) (くすすみじんじゃ)
: A Shikinaisha. Enshrined deities: Ame-no-Kunohi no Mikoto and {{ill|qid=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi|Q8009611|qid=Q8009611|qid=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi no Mikoto|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto}}.
: Formerly located on the riverside east of the current site at Ebisu-yama, it was relocated to the present shrine grounds in Keiō 2.
;Massha Ichikishimahime Shrine (いちきしまひめじんじゃ) and Mononobe Shrine (もののべじんじゃ)
: Enshrined deities: Kashiwaya-hime no Mikoto and Umashimaji no Mikoto; accompanying enshrinement of Mononobe no Moriya no Muraji. Their origins are unknown, but they are said to enshrine the ancestral deities of the shrine families, particularly the Moriya family.
